2009-10: Played in 27 games, starting 18…led the team in steals…ranked second on the squad in assists and third in rebounding…finished sixth in the UAA in steals per game and 11th in assists per game…reached season-high of 13 points in wins over New Jersey City (12/9) and NYU-Poly (11/24)…also had a season-best five steals against New Jersey City…pulled down a career-high 10 rebounds vs. Drew (3/6)…dished out six assists in consecutive games: vs. New Jersey City and FDU-Florham (1/2)…played a career-high 31 minutes vs. Case Western Reserve (1/31)…received the Arthur Ashe, Jr. Sports-Scholar Award. 2008-09: Saw action in 24 games as a reserve…contributed eight points, including a pair of key three-pointers, in 16 minutes at Chicago (2/8)…played a season-high 23 minutes at SUNY New Paltz (12/1) and Carnegie Mellon (2/15)…totaled season highs of nine points and five steals, and added four rebounds vs. FDU-Florham (11/21)…collected a season-best five rebounds vs. Lehman (11/25)…amassed a collegiate-best six steals at Mount St. Mary (11/15). 2007-08: Played in all 25 games, including four starts…led all rookies and ranked second on the team in free-throw percentage…finished third on the team in scoring, assists and steals…reached double digits in scoring seven times…established career highs of 21 points (6-9 FG, 7-7 FT) and seven assists vs. Stevens Tech (12/30)…made her first career start and finished with 14 points vs. Chicago (1/27). High School: Averaged 17.5 ppg, 5.0 apg and 3.0 spg during her senior season…McDonald’s All-American nominee and Second Team All-State selection as a senior…named MVP of the All-State Senior All-Star Game…All-Area honoree as a junior and senior…All-Conference selection as a sophomore, junior and senior…accumulated more than 1,000 points, reaching the millennium mark on senior night…Honor Roll Student…member of the Human Relations Club…DECA Community Service Award recipient…served as an AAU and CYO volunteer…played for four AAU teams: Team CT, the CT Northstars, the CT Breeze, and the CT Starters. Personal: Minoring in event management…earned a scholarship from NYU’s School of Continuing and Professional Studies…enjoys photography, friends and trivia…fan of Steve Nash and the Phoenix Suns…hopes to play professionally overseas and then attend graduate school for sports sociology.
